<HEADLINE>
NO BENEFITS, BUT NO JOBS: WELFARE'S MISSING-IN-ACTION 
</HEADLINE>
  
(Repeating for all needing.) 
 (ATTN: Mass., Wis., N.J.)   (The Week in Review)  
 (bl)  
 By CAREY GOLDBERG   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ They seem to be the disappeared, the missing, the lost
in action of the new welfare era.
</P>
<P>
   As more and more states track down former welfare recipients to
assess how their well-being has been affected by stricter
