<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On a budget? Don't ignore Buick Century
 &HT;    By Linda Sharp
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Are you one of those people who has champagne taste
but a beer budget?
</P>
<P>
   Do you sometimes need space for six adults? Would you really
like the image that goes with a premium, upscale brand?
</P>
<P>
   Reality _ like that for a lot of us _ is that your final
purchase decision is dictated by your budget.
</P>
<P>
   You might want to glance in a direction you might not have
considered _ the Buick Century.
</P>
<P>
   With more youthful, contemporary styling and a host of standard
equipment and innovative design features, the midsize Century has
more trunk space and more interior room than any other car in its
segment, Buick says. It might be a luxury car the masses can
afford.
</P>
<P>
   Standard vehicle pricing begins at $20,145, but a fully equipped
model that includes leather seating, six-way power front seats,
rear seat armrest, cruise control, auto-dimming rearview mirror and
premium-grade stereo with cassette/CD player and
steering-wheel-mounted stereo controls can be had for around
$23,500.
</P>
<P>
   The Century's 3.1-liter V-6 provides ample power, while at the
same time offering 20 mpg around town and up to 29 on the highway.
</P>
<P>
   All-speed traction control is now standard not only on the
Century but on all Buicks. The Buick system works in both forward
and reverse by regulating the engine output to enable traction on
wet roads or in sand, snow or gravel. Four-wheel anti-lock brakes
are also standard.
</P>
<P>
   A really neat feature is the tire inflation monitor. An
indicator on the dash notifies the driver that a tire is losing or
has lost air. It requires an average drop of 8-10 psi to trigger
the monitor, but the warning should enable the driver who has
picked up a slow leak or experienced a minor puncture to be able to
get the tire repaired before it is permanently damaged. It also
will alert those of us who have the bad habit of never checking
their air pressure that it is time to pump the black doughnuts back
up.
</P>
<P>
   A low-pressure tire is much more likely to suffer a failure than
a properly inflated one.
</P>
<P>
   Another timely feature is the Century's air filtration system,
which automatically reduces pollen before it reaches the car's
interior. With pollen numbers in some areas currently off the
scale, this feature alone should be worth a test drive during
pollen season.
</P>
<P>
   Bottom line, the Buick Century is a pleasant car with upscale
amenities that keep your tires on their toes and allow your nose to
breath cleaner air and at a price that many budgets can handle _
all with a premium badge on the grille.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
