<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-03 14:04 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2283 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS &LR;      05-03 0431
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`BABE' ONE OF THE BEST; `MAIL' A TIRED RETREAD 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Babe: Pig in the City'' _ Pound for pound, this
was one of the best pictures of the year. Mired in controversy
because it was hurried into release, ``Babe 2'' never got a fair
shake. This tale does for children's movies what the Brothers Grimm
did for children's literature. Dark, dangerous, and mysterious,
this remarkably well crafted story illuminates the night that most
children fear.
</P>
<P>
   ``You've Got Mail'' _ A love match made in the marketing
department reunites that ``Sleepless in Seattle'' pair _ Tom Hanks
and Meg Ryan _ and tosses in the Internet. How hip. How cool. But
this bland romance should be marked ``return to sender.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The Mummy'' (1932) _ Boris Karloff is brilliant, in spite of
some terrible writing and an overwrought supporting cast. Director
Karl Freund incorporates outlandish lighting effects to generate
the horror. But it's Karloff that makes this B picture an A.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DVD UPDATE: While sales of DVD players continue to mount, along
with the number of titles available on the superior format, the
prices are beginning to rise as well. Both Warner Home Video and
Columbia TriStar Home Video are keeping their prices at $25, but
other companies are releasing discs in the $30-35 range. ``A Bug's
Life,'' one of the most gorgeous of the DVDs released so far, is
marked at a rather hefty $34.99. Since demand remains strong and
disc manufacturers have trouble supplying the demand, it's a trend
that seems bound to continue. According to a survey ordered by
Video Business magazine, the average price of a DVD has risen from
$24.98 to $26.53 in two years. But that's based on suggested retail
price. The on-line services _ such as NetFlix, Amazon.com, and
Empire DVD _ still offer deep discounts.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: May 11: ``Star Trek: Insurrection,''
``Another Day in Paradise,'' ``Velvet Goldmine,'' ``As Time Goes
By'' (BBC), ``Teletubbies Hanging Garden,'' ``Bent,'' ``A Cool, Dry
Place.'' May 18: ``The Imposters,'' ``Batman Beyond: The Movie,''
``Holy Man,'' ``In Dreams,'' ``Memorial Day,'' ``My Sweet
Suicide,'' ``Rowing With the Wind,'' ``Shadow of Doubt.'' May 25:
``Saving Private Ryan,'' ``Gloria,'' ``Forbidden Fruit,''
``Hellcab.'' June 1: ``The Base,'' ``Gunshy.'' June 8: ``From the
Earth to the Moon,'' ``Treehouse Hostage.'' June 22: ``Waking Ned
Devine,'' ``Sweethearts,'' ``Storm of the Century.''
</P>
