   &UR; KOSOVO &LR;  (``i'' code)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times plans 3 pages of stories, photos and graphics
on the continuing crisis in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-DIPLO (Washington) _ President Clinton and Viktor
Chernomyrdin, the Russian envoy, meet on Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Brussels) _ Examining the threshold crossed by NATO
when its attack knocked out electricity in much of Serbia (and
water, too). Also, details of the graphite powder bomb used to
short-circuit a plant without destroying it. By Michael R. Gordon.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-SERBS (Belgrade) _ Talking to people in Belgrade and Novi
Sad about what the stepped-up air campaign means in their daily
lives. By Carlotta Gall.
</P>
<P>
