<HEADLINE>
A CALL TO ARMS
</HEADLINE>
  This separate-buy article can be purchased by calling New York
Times Syndicate sales representative DEBRA WEYDERT at (732)
390-4480 or fax her at (732) 390-4697. Clients of Dr. Brazelton's
Families Today column will get a special discounted price.  
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 World Rights 
 By T. BERRY BRAZELTON, M.D. and JOSHUA SPARROW, M.D.  
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The massacre in Littleton, Colo., is a national tragedy. It is
also a national indictment. It should not be seen as just a high
school tragedy or a breakdown in preventive care for two disturbed
teen-agers. It is an urgent call to our country for help.
</P>
<P>
   The recent episodes of teens and preteens murdering their
classmates have sent a message that our nation is in deep trouble.
We are a violent society. How many more young lives must be lost
before we finally face this?
</P>
<P>
   We are all asking: ``Why did this have to happen?'' We don't
know for sure what drove the two teens in Colorado, but we do know
