   PAINTERS-EYE (London) _ Can artistic talent be measured
scientifically? A laughable notion, perhaps. And yet, according to
``The Painter's Eye,'' an intriguing small show at the National
Portrait Gallery in London that runs through June 13, some of the
secrets of the creative process are now being cracked by the latest
biomedical technology. By Alan Riding.
</P>
