<P>
   COWBOY CAPITAL &QL;
</P>
<P>
   STEPHENVILLE, Texas _ On a cool, misty but sunny morning, Ty
Murray began his day at 7:30, punching cattle on his 1,851-acre
ranch. Within two hours, Murray, a seven-time winner of rodeo's
world all-around title, has doctored a sick mother cow and has
moved a bawling herd of cattle from one pasture to another. He
relishes the rural life near Stephenville, where he and two-time
world bull riding champion Jim Sharp moved nine years ago. What
Murray and Sharp started has become a stampede of rodeo competitors
heading to this town of 14,400. By BRETT HOFFMAN. Story has moved
in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   F I N A N C I A L &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   AIRLINES-UNIONS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Things are tough all over _ at least for
airline executives who are responsible for maintaining working
relationships with their unions. The industry is still hovering
near the peak of its best profits ever. Not surprisingly, workers
industrywide are clamoring for a larger _ and, they believe, fairer
_ share of the profits. And many workers are doing much more than
just clamoring. By DAN REED. Story has moved in ``f'' financial
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
