<P>
   E N T E R T A I N M E N T &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NONFICTION-BOOKLIST &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The Modern Library's just-announced list of the 100
best modern nonfiction books is a definitive list in at least one
sense: It will absolutely make people talk more about books. By
JEFF GUINN. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category.
(Accompanied by NONFICTION-BOOKLIST-LIST.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   C O M M E N T A R Y &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The media can rip Monica Lewinsky all they want. I say
she emerged from a recent interview with a lot more dignity than
Matt Lauer did. Hmm. Is that what's known as damning with faint
praise? By BILL THOMPSON. Story has moved in ``k'' commentary
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
nn
</P>
