<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S `LATE NIGHT WITH CONAN O'BRIEN' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Yahoo.com has started posting a security message on its web site
that warns Internet users to `never assume people online are who
they say they are.' For instance, Yahoo says that most people
online claiming to be 18-year-old girls are actually President
Clinton.
</P>
<P>
   The new high-tech, Star Wars toys are coming out soon. The toys
can talk and are interactive so they can be easily distinguished
from Star Wars fans.
</P>
<P>
   First, reports came out that Pamela Anderson Lee had her breast
implants removed, then yesterday it was reported that she had the
implants replaced with smaller ones. Now today Pamela claims both
reports are false, and that she just had her implants rotated.
</P>
<P>
   Yesterday, the FDA approved a new obesity drug that blocks fat.
In fact, this morning, it wouldn't let Star Jones into work.
</P>
<P>
   Last night in an interview with Connie Chung, Calista Flockhart
said that she's lost four pounds working out, and that she's now in
the best shape of her life. Flockhart said, `I can run the 100 yard
dash in under ten seconds if there is a good wind.'
</P>
<P>
   The Rolling Stones announced that they have changed their minds,
and they will not do a concert at Madison Square Garden this New
Year's Eve. Apparently, the Stones are worried that their pace
makers are not Y2K compatible.
</P>
<P>
   The other day in Florida a 78-year-old man was arrested after he
robbed a bank and led police on a car chase. Actually, it wasn't
really a car chase, it was more like a long slow left turn.
</P>
<P>
   Ripley's Museum wants to get Pamela Anderson Lee's old breast
implants, and put them on display, but it turns out Pamela has
other plans for the implants. She is using them to make a
catamaran.
</P>
<P>
   A brand new book is coming out. It claims that Al Gore smoked a
lot of pot in college. Apparently, you could always tell when Gore
was really high, because he would stare straight ahead, and speak
in monotone.
</P>
<P>
   It was reported today that Michael Jackson's kids also wear
masks when they go out in public. Not because of germs, but because
their father is Michael Jackson.
</P>
<P>
   The `Today' show canceled a scheduled interview with Calista
Flockhart because she said she didn't want to talk about her
weight. Flockhart said instead, she wanted to talk about ricecakes.
</P>
<P>
   Pamela Lee says that since she had surgery to remove her
implants her breasts feel like they're on fire. This is a
coincidence, because Pamela's old implants are now being used to
cushion people jumping out of burning buildings.
</P>
<P>
   Yesterday, Hillary Clinton was principal for a day at a New York
City middle school. Apparently the kids loved it, because they
could all fool around and she had no idea that anything was going
on.
</P>
<P>
   It was reported today that Martha Stewart has contributed a lot
of money to Al Gore's campaign. Not only that, she has also given
Gore tips on how to bring out his rich mahogany finish.
</P>
<P>
   In Ohio, a funeral home worker is in big trouble because he left
a body in the back of a hearse while he hung out at a topless bar.
If that weren't bad enough, on his way home he propped the body up
in the front seat, so he could use the carpool lane.
</P>
<P>
   It was reported this week that Pamela Anderson Lee is getting
back together with rocker Tommy Lee. I think this is a real shame,
because most men were hoping Pamela would get back together with
her implants.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S `THE TONIGHT SHOW WITH JAY LENO' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The following are quotes from Jay Leno's monologue for the week
of April 26, 1999
</P>
<P>
   Monica Lewinsky said today, if they make a TV movie about the
scandal, she wants Neve Campbell to play her. And for Linda Tripp,
I think she wants Ed Asner. President Clinton said today, if they
get Neve Campbell to play Monica, he'll play himself.
</P>
<P>
   The price of gasoline continues to rise in California. Two bucks
a gallon in many places. $2.27 in Beverly Hills. In fact today an
armored car was held up just for the gas.
</P>
<P>
   To show you how time flies, know what happened seven years ago?
The LA riots. And here's a scary thought. Those extended warranties
on those TV's are starting to run out and the HDTV just came in, so
you might want to think about upgrading. It's VCR Independence Day.
</P>
<P>
   The country of Jamaica has approved the growing of hemp to be
used in cat food. In fact, experts said today if a cat spends his
whole life eating hemp cat food, by the time it's five, it will
have a street value of $22,000.
</P>
<P>
   According to a new study, most couples report that sex is better
while on vacation. I'll bet that's why dad never wanted to stop the
car on our way down to the shore. Remember, dad was always in a
hurry to get there, no bathroom breaks, no food, let's just get to
the shore.
</P>
<P>
   I'm 49. I made a decision today. I don't really have any
political affiliation. I'm kinda in the middle, but I'm thinking
maybe I should become a Republican. See if you're a Democrat and
you're 49, you're over the hill, but if you're 49 and a Republican,
you're the youngest guy out there.
</P>
<P>
   According to the latest issue of Nature Biotechnology,
scientists have implanted human DNA into female goats. Is that
really new? I think lonely farmers have been doing that for years.
</P>
<P>
   This is our second night of broadcasting in high-definition
television (April 27). With a high-definition TV everything looks
bigger and wider. It's kind of like going to your 25th high school
reunion.
</P>
