massacre, parents want to know what their teens are up to. So how
far can they go in divining whether their child has a secret life?
Can they barge into his room unannounced and without knocking? Can
they search his room when he's not home? Read his diary? And how do
teens feel about this invasion of privacy? By HANK HUGHES. Story
will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
