INTERNET-SEXOFFENDERS - The eerie galleries of photos are just a
few mouse clicks away on the Internet. Rapists, child molesters and
flashers stare out from the screen. You can find their names,
addresses, ages and descriptions of their crimes. There's the
Chandler, Ariz., man who spent 10 years in prison for attempted sex
acts with a 10-year-old. A few more clicks lead to the Yuma man
convicted of sexual abuse and attempted sexual assault, who was
jailed two years ago for failing to register as a sex offender. You
can check out molesters in Michigan, rapists in North Carolina and
Alaska's 1,600-plus sex offenders. It's all part of a national rush
to use the Internet to alert the public to the identity and
whereabouts of registered sex offenders. At last count, 15 states
were listing sex offenders on websites, with more in the pipeline.
By KATHLEEN INGLEY. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
STRONGARM CHIP (Phoenx) - Intel reveals details about the StrongArm
chip that's being developed in Chandler, Ariz. By REBECCA ROLWING.
Story moved move in the ``F'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) - I missed seeing ``Star Wars'' when it
was released in 1977. It was an innocent thing that has developed
into a solemn crusade. All the hype surrounding the films in the
series led me to vow never to see any of them, to plant myself on
the shore of American popular culture and not be swept away by
George Lucas's tidal wave. To boldly declare, ``The Chewbacca stops
here.'' It hasn't been easy. By E.J. MONTINI. Story moved in the
``A'' and ``K'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
COMPUTER-COLUMN (Phoenix) - What say we learn how to design a Web
page? &QL; 
Aah, come on! It's easy! At least it's easier than filling out your
annual income tax returns.Why should you bother creating your own
Web page? I can think of several reasons. Here are two:1) The Web
is an invaluable tool for communicating with people in your
neighborhood and around the world. Be a part of it!2) You might
already have free ``Web space'' at your disposal. By DAVID HOYE.
Story moved in the ``F'' category. &QL; 
