<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Tuesday, May 4, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   NOAH-TV-MEDIA _ Many viewers of NBC's ``Noah's Ark'' miniseries
cringed, with many flooding the network with calls about the
literary license in the show's adaptation of the Bible story.
According to the program, which garned 50 million viewers, ark
maker Noah was on the scene of Sodom and Gomorrah's destruction, an
event the Bible says happened hundreds of years after the great
flood. By Fred Shuster. (Will move in the ``n'' California and
``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-COLISEUM (Los Angeles) _ Bringing an NFL expansion team to
the Los Angeles Coliseum could cost as much as $348 million in
public contributions, including $85 million in land, $110 million
in earthquake retrofitting and a $113 million Harbor Freeway
improvement. The deal the NFL is considering also could include a
ticket surcharge. By Rick Orlov. (Will move in the ``n'' California
and ``s'' sports news files.)
</P>
<P>
   SMOG-SUBSIDY (Los Angeles) _ With $20 million to help poor
motorists make smog repairs, the DMV triggered a crush of
applicants Monday across the San Fernando Valley and the state by
cutting the copayment from $250 to $75. The copayment was reduced
because only 72 motorists have applied for the subsidy so far. By
Robert Monroe. (Will move in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LLOYD-COLUMN _ Let the hire beware. Daily News columnist Ken
Lloyd, Ph.D., a specialist in organizational behavior, answers
readers' questions on workplace ethics and relationships.
</P>
