   (gm) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times plans 3 pages of stories, photos and graphics
on the continuing crisis in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO (Pec, Yugoslavia) _ A reporter's impressions of hell:
Dying animals, burning buildings. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-DIPLO (Washington) _ President Clinton and Viktor
Chernomyrdin, the Russian envoy, meet on Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Brussels, Belgium) _ Examining the threshold
crossed by NATO when its attack knocked out electricity in much of
Serbia (and water, too). Also, details of the graphite powder bomb
used to short-circuit a plant without destroying it. By Michael R.
Gordon.
